# Install a Infinium CLI Wallet (Ubuntu)

**Step 1**

Go to the official site: https://infinium.space and navigate to the downloads section

**Step 2**

Download Linux (Ubuntu 22.04+) CLI Wallet

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-3](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-3.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-3")

**Step 3**

Right click the file and select Properties

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-4](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-4.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-4")

**Step 4**

Copy the file name

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-5](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-5.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-5")

**Step 5**

Open a terminal in this directory & validate the authenticity of the file by running a checksum (XXX represents your version):

```
sha256sum infinium-linux-x64-v<XXX>.tar.bz2
```

(Results should match release notes from Download page)

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-6-1](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-6-1.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-6-1")
![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-6-2](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-6-2.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-6-2")

**Step 6**

If checksums match, decompress & extract the .tar.bz2 file:

```
tar -xvjf infinium-linux-x64-release-devtools-v1.5.0.143[336fac2].tar.bz2
```

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-7](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-7.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-7")

**Steps 7-9**

1. Delete your original .tar.bz2 file
2. Move the Infinium folder to a location of your choice
3. Within the Infinium directory, open a terminal and run the daemon to start the node and download the blockchain:

```
./infiniumd
```

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-8-10-1](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-8-10-1.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-8-10-1")
![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-8-10-2](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-8-10-2.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-8-10-2")

**Step 11**

Wait for the blockchain to download and sync. This may take quite a few hours, depending on your download speed. And leave the daemon running! We’ll need that to create our new wallet.

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-11](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-11.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-11")

**Step 12**

Once sync is complete, open another terminal in the infinium directory with the simplewalletbinary—that's our CLI wallet executable. Give command:

```
./simplewallet --generate-new-wallet=name.wallet
```

Replace “name” with your new wallet’s name, e.g.,:

```
./simplewallet --generate-new-wallet=infiniumcli.wallet
```

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-12](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-12.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-12")

**Step 13**

When asked, enter a password for your wallet. You should use a password generator, found in password managers such as KeePass.

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-13](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-13.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-13")

**Steps 14-15**

14. To open your new wallet, give the following command in the same terminal (again, substituting "name"):

```
./simplewallet --wallet-file name.wallet
```

15. Enter your password, when prompted. Notice that the wallet displays your receive address after “Opened wallet.” You will use this to fund your new wallet.

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-15](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-15.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-15")

**Steps 16-17**

16. Now we must get our wallet’s seed phrase, as well as set an additional password for the seed itself. Give the command:

```
show_seed
```

17. Again, when prompted provide a password for the seed phrase you’re about to get. Confirm the password, and be sure to save both it and your seed phrase!!

![alt install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-17](../../../static/img/use/install-infinium-cli-wallet-ubuntu/install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-17.png "install-infinium-cli-wallet-step-17")

**You've successfully installed your new Infinium Wallet!**